cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about computing the dynamics of robots and evaluating the method on a 7 degree of freedom robot arm.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses using auto-differentiation toolboxes to learn the dynamics parameters of the robot from data via gradient descent.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with physical constraints in the learning of robot dynamics, which is a key aspect of control systems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses using machine learning techniques to learn physically plausible dynamics models.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper evaluates the method on real-time inverse dynamics predictions, which could involve visual feedback from cameras or sensors.
